TextChange: This can go in the work place as well, everyone at work wants to do a good job at there work place, everybody wants to be on top and get a pat on the back, but it can also turn into a competition instead of a cooperation as well. Because one person may be good in certain fields and another person may not be, but the person that is not good will turn it into a competition for that person that is good at there job, and that person will try to out do the person that is good at what they do, and that can also lead to stress and over worked, and it can make you tired because you are so focused on trying to keep up with that one person at work because you want to be at top as well and be noticed and be told that you did a good job. Some times we don't always get a pat on the back, but that is okay, you just have to know that you are good at what you do, and eventually you will get noticed, you may not get noticed right away, but maybe a year from now or a month or two everybody will start to notice a good job you have done for the company or your work space. \n
Especially in competitions, because you can practice for hours and hours and you still may loose or win. \n
Trust me that is not a good feeling to be left at the bottom.
